# =============================================================================
# CODEOWNERS — Automatic Review Assignment
# =============================================================================
#
# PURPOSE:
#   When a pull request modifies files matching these patterns, the listed
#   owners are AUTOMATICALLY added as reviewers. Combined with branch
#   protection rules requiring reviews, this ensures the right people
#   review the right code.
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
#   - Patterns are matched top-to-bottom; later rules override earlier ones
#   - The "*" pattern matches everything (default owner)
#   - More specific patterns (e.g., ".github/workflows/") take priority
#   - Owners can be GitHub usernames, team slugs (@org/team), or emails
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
#   Security-sensitive files (CI workflows, MCP server, security policies)
#   should always be reviewed by security-aware team members — not just
#   whoever happens to be available.
#
# =============================================================================

# --- Default owner for all files ---
# If no more specific rule matches, this person/team reviews.
# Update this to your team or team lead.
* @sautalwar

# --- CI/CD Workflows ---
# Workflow files control what runs in CI and have access to secrets.
# A malicious workflow change could exfiltrate secrets or deploy
# compromised code. These MUST be reviewed carefully.
.github/workflows/ @sautalwar

# --- Dependabot & GitHub Config ---
# Changes to Dependabot config, Actions permissions, or other
# GitHub-specific configuration files.
.github/ @sautalwar

# --- MCP Server ---
# The MCP server has access to external systems (Jira, etc.).
# Changes here could introduce data exfiltration or injection risks.
mcp-server/ @sautalwar

# --- Security Policy ---
# Changes to the security policy affect how vulnerabilities are reported
# and handled. Must be reviewed by a security-aware team member.
SECURITY.md @sautalwar

# --- Security Documentation ---
# Ensuring security guidance stays accurate and up-to-date.
docs/security/ @sautalwar

# --- Gitleaks Configuration ---
# Changes to secret scanning rules could weaken detection.
.gitleaks.toml @sautalwar

# =============================================================================
# CUSTOMIZATION FOR YOUR TEAM
# =============================================================================
#
# For larger teams, use GitHub team slugs:
#   .github/workflows/ @your-org/platform-team @your-org/security-team
#   mcp-server/        @your-org/ai-team @your-org/security-team
#   src/main/java/     @your-org/backend-team
#
# For specific file types:
#   *.sql              @your-org/dba-team
#   Dockerfile         @your-org/platform-team
#   pom.xml            @your-org/backend-team
#
